The '''Statesboro Northern Railway''' began operating in 1924 on 44 miles of former [[Midland Railway (Georgia)|Midland Railway]] between [[Statesboro, Georgia]] and [[Stevens Crossing, Georgia]]. It was immediately leased by the [[Georgia and Florida Railroad (1926-1971)|Georgia and Florida Railway]], and was completely abandoned in 1950.
